is it wrong to catch a fly then tie a thread to his foot and fly him like a kite i find all of your answers interesting and i found it fascinating how easily most of you found it interesting and funny that this was being done to a living creature it also occurred to me how easy it was for most of you to just dismiss the life of a fly as completely unimportant and expendable it also occurred to me that this is the same mentality that allowed michael vick to do what he did to dogs i am not saying that what you are doing is equal to what he has done what i am saying is the attitude towards a living creature be it a fly or a dog is the same interesting how as human beings we feel we have the right to decide the worth of an animals life and whether we should destroy it or protect it Sesshomaru Alignment (role-playing games) Animal rights Gray Wolf The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Tertiary to Quintessential Phases Kitesurfing W.I.T.C.H. Pern Vampire Zoophilia Goodness and value theory Simone Weil Seventh Sea (collectible card game) Glen Jacobs Peter Singer Creatures in Bionicle Spidey Super Stories Theory of conduct Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Space Shuttle program Avengers (comics) Roswell UFO incident Abortion debate Scrapped Princess Abduction Phenomenon Chaos (video game) Shaggy dog story Wolf's Rain Socrates Gulliver's Travels Sant Mat The Death Gate Cycle The Amber Spyglass Fancy rat The Subtle Knife Fictional character Speciesism Borg Obedience training Falconry Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Meaning of life Force (Star Wars) Monty Python's Flying Circus Xenomorph Pikmin Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Alien races from the Godzilla films Theodicy Ethics Extraterrestrial life Mach kernel Biblical inerrancy Unidentified flying object Zagreus (Doctor Who audio) Occam's Razor Fox hunting Angels in Islam Atheism Monty Python Tukaram Softball Chimpanzee Asperger syndrome Baseball Nuclear warfare Homunculus Stuttering Futurama (TV series - sea